1321 /// Currently, we also refuse to change the precise type used for an atomic or
1322 /// volatile store. This is debatable, and might be reasonable to change later.
1323 /// However, it is risky in case some backend or other part of LLVM is relying
1324 /// on the exact type stored to select appropriate atomic operations.
1325 ///
1326 /// \returns true if the store was successfully combined away. This indicates
